Package net.sf.jstuff.core.logging

Interface Logger

public interface Logger
Features:
  • Logger implementation using the Formatter syntax for message templates.
  • entry() logs parameter name and parameter values.
  • Stacktraces are logged truncated if logger is not at DEBUG level.
  • fatal(java.lang.Throwable)() always logs the full stacktrace
  • Defaults to SLF4J as logging infrastructure and falls back to java.util.logging if SLF4J is not available.
    • Author:
    Sebastian Thomschke
